This paper is about person Re-identification (ReID) which is a computer vision task, so it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) category. The paper proposes a novel network structure and a method for model fine-tuning, which involves training a pre-trained model on a new dataset. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. Additionally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in Multimedia (cs.MM) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) research. Finally, the paper addresses the challenge of variations in the target scenario, which is related to the topic of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
